{"id": 225003726, "title": "Free Euros 2024 fan zones to be set up in heart of Glasgow for hundreds to watch games for free", "text": "A fan zone in the heart of Glasgow city centre will show Scotland's Euro 2024 group games - for free. Hundreds of fans will be able to take in the action in the courtyard within Merchant Square. Tennent's is sponsoring the fan zone, which will have seating for 300 fans in the square, with the matches shown on a new 13k laser projector. Steve Clarke's men feature in the opening match of the tournament, taking on hosts Germany at the Allianz Arena, the home stadium of Bayern Munich, on Friday, June 14, in Munich. On Wednesday, June 19, Scotland v Switzerland, in Cologne, will be shown at the fan zone. And on Sunday, June 23, the Scotland b Hungary clash from Stuttgart will be broadcast. Before each fixture, fans will be treated to pre- match entertainment by local singer-songwriter, Kirk Strachan, who is known for his melodic rock style and eclectic range of influences. He will be entertaining the crowd from 6pm on Scotland match days, with the fan zone open from 5pm to 11pm over the month-long tournament. Seating is on a first come, first served basis and, if the seating area is full, fans can book tables in the many bars and restaurants within Merchant Square, such as Bar Soba, Metropolitan, O\u2019Neill\u2019s, Pania, Sano, Table Twenty-Eight and The Tap Yard. Fans can access drinks and food from each of the venues in the Square from the fan zone. Only over 18s are allowed in the fan zone, and drinks will be served in plastic, cans, or polycarbonate \u2013 no glass will be used in the central area. Merchant Square's Julie Edwin said: \"For those unable to make the pilgrimage to Germany, we're delighted to be hosting the Merchant Square Euro 2024 Fanzone \u2013 sponsored by Tennent's - a hub for all Scotland fans! \"Entry to the Fan zone is free, and you'll be guaranteed a great atmosphere. Good luck Scotland!\" Merchant Square is located in Glasgow's Merchant City area, with entrances on the corner of Candleriggs and Bell Street and Albion Street. Don't miss the latest news from around Scotland and beyond - Sign up to our daily newsletter here.", "summary": "Merchant Square, in Glasgow city centre, will be showing Steve Clarke's men in action against Germany, Switzerland and Hungary.", "url": "https://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/news/scottish-news/free-euros-2024-fan-zones-32913112", "image": "https://i2-prod.dailyrecord.co.uk/incoming/article32901735.ece/ALTERNATES/s1200/0_JS262083077.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-29 12:10:59", "author": "Rory Cassidy", "authors": ["Rory Cassidy"], "language": "en", "source_country": "gb", "sentiment": 0.588}